Granted
Reasoning: Although there are some discrepancies with the dates when the persecution took place, it is clear that the appellant was persecuted by the Nigerian government for their political beliefs. They have provided a consistent account of being detained twice, beaten and accused of supporting Biafran separatists. This is supported by medical evidence of scarring, and corroborated by their partner who was also arrested and ill-treated. I find that this is sufficient evidence to show that the appellant has a well-founded fear of future persecution. Given the serious nature of the harm suffered by them and their partner, and the fact that the authorities continue to target members of IPOB in Nigeria, I am satisfied that they will be at risk on return."
